    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="1167"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1167">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/10</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-18T23:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 19, 7 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>403. I have just received the following cipher telegram from <persName
                        corresp="#p_GJW2">Gerard</persName> at Berlin:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>Please inform British Government that I advise them to allow no Germans to
                        leave England or any British Dominions until I obtain leave British subjects
                        to leave Germany.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>This seems to me too important a subject to act on without explicit instructions
                    from our Government. I hold awaiting instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                            <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                        </persName>)</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center">[Telegram]</note>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-19">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1914</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Your 403. Department deems it inadvisable to comply with suggestion of
                        Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">Gerard</persName> as such compliance
                        would be inconsistent with neutral attitude assumed by this Government.
                        Department has cabled Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_GJW2"
                            >Gerard</persName>.</p>
                    <closer rendition="#right">
                        <signed>
                            <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                            </persName>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2" type="to">
                            <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>)</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center">[Telegram]</note>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1914-08-20T15:00:00-05:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Department is informed by Ambassador at London that he has received following
                        telegram from you.</p>
                    <p>Please inform British Government that I advise them to allow no Germans to
                        leave England or any British Dominions until I obtain leave British subjects
                        to leave Germany.</p>
                    <p>Department is of the opinion that such an exchange of communications should
                        not be made through the good offices of the United States.</p>
                    <p rend="right">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
